@startuml
title Export Court List v2.1 (multiple court sites per XML file)

' Change Log

' v2
' * Publishing Court Lists now saves the list to the 'published_court_list' table
' * XML files contain Court Lists for all Court Sites for the Parent Court
' * XML files are generated from Published Court Lists
' * The COURT_LIST_PRODUCED state is removed
' * The fileservice is removed

' Diagram changes
' * Status updates have been removed for clarity

' v2.1
' * Export is triggered by a scheduler to remove the race condition

JavaTimer -> JavaTimer: sleep 10 minutes

' Export
JavaTimer->CourtListEventProcessor: findPublishedCourtListsWaitingForExport
CourtListEventProcessor -> ListingQueryView: listing.publishedcourtlist query
ListingQueryView-> published_court_list: findCourtListsRequiringExport

loop every court list requiring export
CourtListEventProcessor -> ListingCommandHandler: listing.command.court-lists.request-export (courtSite)
ListingCommandHandler -> CourtListEventProcessor: listing.command.court-lists.export-requested

' XML generation
CourtListEventProcessor -> ListingQueryView: listing.query.published-courtlists (parentCourt)

ListingQueryView -> published_court_list: retrievePublishedCourtLists

CourtListEventProcessor -> CourtListEventProcessor: generateXmlCourtListForParentCourt()

CourtListEventProcessor -> XhibitService: sendToExhibit

XhibitService -> WebDAV: PUT file
CourtListEventProcessor -> ListingCommandHandler :listing.command.record-court-list-export-successful
end
@enduml
